```cpp
#include <hexi/hexi.h>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <cstdint>

struct NetworkPacket {
    uint32_t packet_id;
    std::string username;
    std::vector<uint32_t> scores;
    std::string metadata;

    void serialise(auto& stream) {
        // Write packet_id (POD type, will be written directly)
        stream << packet_id;

        // Write username with length prefix using prefixed adaptor
        stream << hexi::prefixed(username);

        // Write scores vector with count first, then elements using operator<<
        // The operator<< for prefixed containers will handle this automatically
        stream << hexi::prefixed(scores);

        // Write metadata as null-terminated string using null_terminated adaptor
        stream << hexi::null_terminated(metadata);
    }
};

std::vector<uint8_t> serialize_packet(const NetworkPacket& packet) {
    // Create a buffer to hold the serialized data
    std::vector<uint8_t> buffer;

    // Create a buffer_adaptor for the buffer
    hexi::buffer_adaptor<std::vector<uint8_t>> adaptor(buffer);

    // Create a binary_stream using the buffer_adaptor
    hexi::binary_stream<decltype(adaptor)> stream(adaptor);

    // Create a copy of the packet since serialise modifies the object
    NetworkPacket packet_copy = packet;

    // Call the serialise method on the packet copy using the stream
    packet_copy.serialise(stream);

    // Return the populated buffer
    return buffer;
}
```

## Key Implementation Points:

1. **Packet ID Serialization**: Used `stream << packet_id` which will serialize as POD type (direct memory copy).

2. **Username Serialization**: Used `hexi::prefixed(username)` adaptor which automatically writes the length prefix followed by the string data.

3. **Scores Vector Serialization**: Used `hexi::prefixed(scores)` which writes the count first (as uint32_t) followed by all elements using `write_container`.

4. **Metadata Serialization**: Used `hexi::null_terminated(metadata)` which writes the string data followed by a null terminator.

5. **Buffer Management**: Created `buffer_adaptor` to adapt the `std::vector<uint8_t>` buffer and `binary_stream` to handle the serialization operations.

6. **Copy Handling**: Created a copy of the packet since the `serialise` method modifies the object state during serialization.

This implementation follows all the specified requirements and uses the Hexi library functions as documented in the reference materials.

